            <h4>The End is The Beginning</h4>
              <p>Snail&rsquo;s new album, &ldquo;Terminus,&rdquo; showcases all fresh material, infused with the enthusiasm of newly minted collaboration. Influences that were not evident in past works come to the fore, steeped in early-eighties proto-metal and psychedelia. The subject matter is noticeably more mature, as the entire record delves into the themes of mortality and its implications in our modern world. The name Terminus is latin and translates as &quot;boundary stone.&quot; It signifies both the death of the old Self/World and the birth of the new, as represented by the cover art depicting Nature blasting through one of the great icons of Civilization. From crushing doom to head-bobbing Camaro rock and hypnotic psych, &ldquo;Terminus&rdquo; is Snail&rsquo;s most varied work to date, rife with meaning and hidden messages; but most importantly, IT ROCKS.</p>
<p>"<em>High on my list of most-anticipated 2012 releases</em>" - The Obelisk</p>
